-926689196.text: "In conclusion, prednisone, ibuprofen and betamethasone may prevent OA by suppressing the expression of IL-6 and IL-8, subsequently inactivating NF-kappaB and STAT3 pathways, and ultimately, leading to decreased levels of collagen I, MMP-1, and MMP-13."
